    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the base of your<strong> lettuce</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>lettuce </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the<strong> lettuce leaves</strong> from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves and add to a large bowl with the <strong>remaining red wine vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a gentle mix – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
